parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erratic fuel gauge readings can cause the rider to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to a sudden loss of power and potential accidents, especially on high-speed roads or remote areas.
symptoms: The fuel gauge provides inaccurate or erratic readings
sometimes showing empty
full
or random levels; the gauge stops functioning suddenly; the gauge does not register fuel levels accurately
leading to unexpected fuel depletion.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine loses power
stalls
or runs roughly
often accompanied by surging or hesitation. The vehicle may be difficult to control or come to a sudden stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive heat from the exhaust pipe can cause burns or fires, potentially resulting in serious injuries.
symptoms: The exhaust pipe is excessively hot
causing burns or fires
especially when in close proximity to flammable materials such as clothing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake master cylinder can cause a loss of braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when slowing down or stopping.
symptoms: The rear brake pedal goes completely down against its hard stop
no braking occurs
vibration or shuddering when depressing the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped rotors can cause vibration or shuddering when braking, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vibration or shuddering when depressing the brake pedal
uneven brake pedal feel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front wheel wobble can cause loss of control, especially when braking, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The front wheel feels wobbly or unstable
the wobble gets worse when braking
difficulty controlling the bike
especially at high speeds or when exiting highways.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Head Bearing Loosening on Triple Clamp to Frame
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loosening of the head bearings on the triple clamp to frame can cause the handlebars to become unstable, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The handlebars feel loose or unstable
the front end of the motorcycle wanders or shakes while riding
the steering feels uneven or difficult to control.
